headline: Intel’s Foundry Pivot Deepens With Apple Talks And New U.S. Stake
summary: Intel (NasdaqGS:INTC) is in discussions with Apple and Nvidia about using its U.S. foundry network for chip manufacturing and advanced packaging, as part of a broader supply chain diversification away from TSMC. The U.S. government has taken a direct ownership stake in Intel, marking an unusual level of federal involvement in a major semiconductor company. Both developments highlight Intel's push to expand its foundry business and reinforce its role in U.S. chip production policy. For you...

headline: Elon Musk Bets On Optimus—But Prediction Markets Take The Other Side
summary: The era of Tesla Inc (NASDAQ:TSLA) as just a car company may be just about over. CEO Elon Musk announced during the Q4 earnings call that the company will end production of its flagship Model S and Model X vehicles next quarter. Musk called the decision an “honorable discharge” for the vehicles that put Tesla on the map. But for investors, the message is far more aggressive: Tesla is focusing on what Musk says is the biggest product in history: the Optimus humanoid robot. Don't Miss: Missed Nvid
